	<Title>
		Recipe: Fruit and nut bar
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		This fruit and nut bar is much healthier than a candy bar.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		10
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip: &lt;/strong&gt;This treat is much healthier than a candy bar &amp;mdash; count it as your sweet treat for the day.
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Combine all ingredients, mix well. Spread half an inch thick over a parchment-lined sheet pan. Bake at 300 F for 20 minutes. Cool completely and cut.
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup quinoa flour&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup oats&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup flax meal&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup wheat germ&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup chopped almonds&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup dried apricots&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup chopped dried figs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup buckwheat honey&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/4 cup chopped dried pineapple&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 tablespoons cornstarch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
